\mathbf{C}_{\\mathbb{B}^{n},q}(x;t_{x})$ for\nany $x\\in\\mathbb{B}^{n}\\backslash\\{0\\}$, and\n$\\mathbf{C}_{\\mathbb{H}^{n},q}(x)=\\mathbf{C}_{\\mathbb{H}^{n},q}(x;t_{e_{n}})$\nfor any $x\\in \\mathbb{H}^{n}$. Here $t_{w}$ denotes any unit vector in\n$\\mathbb{R}^{n}$\n  such that $\\langle t_{w},w\\rangle=0$ for $w\\in \\mathbb{R}^{n}\\setminus\\{0\\}$.\n\\end{abstract}\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 21 Sep 2020 00:10:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-24"}
